# Juice Shop Vulnerability Testing Tools

This repository hosts a set of tools specifically designed for testing security vulnerabilities in the OWASP Juice Shop application. These tools aim to facilitate the identification and remediation of security flaws in a controlled educational environment.

#Prerequisites

Before you begin, make sure you have the following installed on your system:

- **Kali Linux (or any Linux distribution)**
- **Node.js and npm** - Needed for running Juice Shop.
- **Python 3.7 or higher** - Required for the scanning tools.
- **Git** - Used for cloning repositories.

#Check installations by running:

node -v
npm -v
python3 --version

#Installing Juice Shop

Step 1: Clone the Juice Shop Repository

Open your terminal and execute:

git clone https://github.com/juice-shop/juice-shop.git
cd juice-shop

Step 2: Install Dependencies

npm install

Step 3: Start the Juice Shop Application

npm start

Juice Shop will be running at http://localhost:3000. Open this URL in your browser to confirm it's operational.

#Setting Up the Scanning Tools

Unzipping the Tool:
If youâ€™ve received the tool as a .zip file:


unzip your-tool-name.zip -d your-tool-directory
cd your-tool-directory

Install Required Python Libraries:

pip install -r requirements.txt

The requirements.txt should list necessary libraries like requests, beautifulsoup4, etc.

#Running the Tools

Run the Main Script:
Execute the main scanning script:

python3 main.py

Select Scanning Options:
The tool may prompt you to input:

    Target URL: http://localhost:3000 (for scanning the locally running Juice Shop).

